Senior Advisor to the President Jared Kushner, Assistant to the President and Special Representative for International Negotiations Jason Greenblatt, and United States Consul General in Jerusalem Donald Blome met with President Mahmoud Abbas of the Palestinian Authority and his senior advisors in Ramallah. The meeting was productive and both sides reaffirmed their commitment to President Trump's goal of achieving a genuine and lasting peace between Israelis and Palestinians. They discussed the priorities for the Palestinians and potential next steps, including the need for economic opportunities and investments in the Palestinian economy. The officials emphasized that peace will take time and stressed the importance of creating a conducive environment for peacemaking. Kushner and Greenblatt will return to Washington to brief President Trump, Secretary Tillerson, and General McMaster and continue the conversation about next steps.